<title>JAPAN: NCB problem loans total 1.26 trln yen as of March.</title>
<headline>NCB problem loans total 1.26 trln yen as of March.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nippon Credit Bank Ltd (NCB) said on Tuesday that its outstanding problem loans totalled 1.26 trillion yen as of the end of March 1997.</p>
<p>The bank said in a statement that, of the total, combined bad and non-performing loans amounted to 940 billion yen and restructured loans stood at 260 billion yen. Outstanding loans to troubled clients totalled 60 billion yen.</p>
